Here's how I connect the the TTY to an RS-232 Port:

1.  Purchase a RS-232C to 20ma Current Loop Converter from Global Computer
Supplies.

2.  Hook the converter to the RS-232 Port using a null modem cable.

3.  Connect the "Receive" loop on the teletype to the "Input" side of the
converter.

4.  Connect the "Transmit" loop on the teletype to the "Output" side of
the converter.

5.  Set the RS-232 port as follows:  110 baud, no parity, 7 data bits, 2
stop bits

6.  Enjoy!

