This was from March 1980.  Luser simply meant user, with the
implication that all users were losers.  A tourist (often spelled
turist) was someone who had no connection with MIT.  We had a T show
up by our name, and we were chased away whenever there were more than
about 15 users on.  There were only 11 here, but only because this was
