permanently deleted in June 1984 for simply mentioning the net in his
Byte column.

Some golden age.

A friend of mine almost had his account denied because his username,
which was his nickname, sounded like it might be a company.  Ellen
Golden (sp?) was prescient, as DIGEX (Doug Humphrey) did indeed, a
decade later, turn his nickname into a multi-million dollar business.

