implementation looks like, nor even how it's done - if it works
by the book, only that it run and "feel" like a -10 should.  Remember
that the vast majority of -10 programmers may never have seen the
machine they were working on (it being in the large cold room), so
they have no preconceived notions of what the box should look like.

