period for a file type is archaic and should have been rendered totally
obsolete long ago.  This is one of the few things that MacOS got right.

The entire problem with extensions on MS platforms today is *NOT* that
they conflict with the PDP-10 (let's be honest, very few people care any
longer) but rather that it overrides defined Internet typing mechanisms
and provides fertile ground for security breaches.  That problem would
exist even if MS rigidly adhered to every DEC naming convention ever
established, even the most obscure ones from the PDP-15.

There's plenty to bash MS about, but incompatibility of file extensions
with the PDP-10 is not one of them.  I wish that it were, but it really
isn't.

